    {
      "id": 42,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": {
        "0": 46,
        "1": -272
      },
      "size": {
        "0": 573.2476196289062,
        "1": 254.3040313720703
      },
      "flags": {},
      "order": 5,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "step 1. \n\n-Bypass all other groups.\n-Load video.\n-Queue prompt.\n-Copy first frame to clipboard.\n-If you require audio, connect the audio output to the audio connection node.\n\n-Bypass this node and proceed to step 2."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": {
        "0": -647,
        "1": 953
      },
      "size": {
        "0": 573.2476196289062,
        "1": 254.3040313720703
      },
      "flags": {},
      "order": 6,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "step 2. \n\n- Bypass other groups.\n- Paste the first frame from clip space into the load image node.\n- Choose a control net that maintains the position of the face in the frame. Open pose and line art are effective.\n- Run image to image multiple times until you achieve the desired animation of facial motion on the character. You can copy the output image to clip space and paste it back into the load image to enhance the style/face shape while keeping the framing and size close to the 1st frame.\n- Copy the output image from the preview image node and proceed to step 3.\n---\nI recommend a 1:1 ratio because it works best with the live portrait nodes. "
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": {
        "0": 885,
        "1": -271
      },
      "size": {
        "0": 573.2476196289062,
        "1": 254.3040313720703
      },
      "flags": {},
      "order": 7,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "step 3. \n\n-Bypass groups 2 and 4.\n-Paste the I2I output image from ClipSpace into the load image node.\n-Queue the prompt to load the source's first frame and match the expression. Edit if necessary! (The first frame is where all the tracking points will map. If they have their mouth open, increase the 'aaa'; if they are smiling, increase the 'smile', etc.). You will need to queue the prompt or set it on automatic queue. (It is important to bypass the other groups!)\n-Adjust the upscale image node if you are using a different aspect ratio.\n\n-Once you have matched the expression and head position, proceed to step 4."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": {
        "0": 1656,
